Yeah, put your hands together
for these hardworking musicians.

31:20.255 --> 31:23.300
Ladies and gentlemen,
my name is Dave Debusher.

31:23.383 --> 31:24.551
Dandy Dave!

31:24.635 --> 31:26.637
That's right. Dandy Dave Debusher.

31:26.720 --> 31:28.055
And this morning I had the pleasure

31:28.138 --> 31:30.974
of giving away my daughter
to a man who don't deserve her.

31:31.058 --> 31:32.059
Daddy.

31:32.142 --> 31:36.021
But who may grow to--
who may grow to deserve her.

31:36.688 --> 31:38.732
Lisey says he's gonna be a great writer.

31:38.815 --> 31:42.444
Something about magical surrealism.

31:43.403 --> 31:44.655
I got my doubts.

31:47.074 --> 31:50.285
But Lisey says
he's got a contract on this book.

31:52.829 --> 31:55.916
And he's bound for the stars,
and that's good enough for me and Ma.

31:56.875 --> 31:58.877
He went on like that all night.

32:00.254 --> 32:02.214
Oh, he loved you, hon.

32:02.297 --> 32:03.423
He was drunk.

32:03.507 --> 32:05.926
Yeah. And he loved you.

32:10.055 --> 32:11.348
Why a bool hunt?

32:12.474 --> 32:13.517
Why now?

32:15.435 --> 32:16.812
What did your brother call it?

32:18.355 --> 32:19.773
Is it a blood-bool?

32:21.608 --> 32:22.609
It's coming.

32:25.696 --> 32:28.282
But right now
you need to take care of Amanda.

32:29.783 --> 32:33.453
Follow the clues and get your prize.

32:33.537 --> 32:34.538
If you'll just indulge me,

32:34.621 --> 32:37.207
I'd like to get this wonderful
young couple for one more dance.

32:37.291 --> 32:38.292
Come on.

32:38.375 --> 32:40.127
