33:06.028 --> 33:08.238
Scott? Scott?

33:11.200 --> 33:12.326
Come back!

33:18.582 --> 33:21.084
Good lovin'
All I need is lovin'

33:21.168 --> 33:22.377
Good lovin'

33:40.312 --> 33:41.396
Amanda?

33:42.272 --> 33:43.649
Amanda?

33:44.775 --> 33:45.943
Amanda?

34:04.753 --> 34:06.004
Amanda?

34:14.263 --> 34:15.264
Manda?

34:19.268 --> 34:20.268
Hey.

34:20.893 --> 34:21.895
Hey.

34:24.898 --> 34:28.610
Hey. Big sissa, Manda-Bunny, hey.

34:28.694 --> 34:30.320
Let's go back to bed.

34:32.572 --> 34:33.782
Okay?

34:37.034 --> 34:39.454
We're closing, sir. Soon.

34:39.538 --> 34:42.748
Do you know this was Scott Landon's
favorite book when he was a kid?

34:44.668 --> 34:46.335
Finally got around to reading it.

34:47.004 --> 34:48.797
No, I didn't know that.

34:49.672 --> 34:51.967
Well, you must--
you must have known him, right?

34:52.050 --> 34:54.094
Didn't he pay for this library?

34:54.761 --> 34:56.096
I knew him to speak to him,

34:56.179 --> 34:58.473
but I-- I knew his wife better.

34:58.557 --> 35:00.809
Lisa. Lisey.

35:00.893 --> 35:04.479
Yeah, she used to come in often.
Sometimes she read to the children.

35:05.981 --> 35:09.318
Actually, I believe
it was she who funded the--

35:09.401 --> 35:10.819
No, the money came from him.

35:12.654 --> 35:14.364
Didn't it? Everything came from him.

35:15.032 --> 35:17.784
Well, I suppose so.
In a manner of speaking--

35:17.868 --> 35:19.453
Ain't no manner about it.

35:20.579 --> 35:21.997
Everything came from him.

35:23.207 --> 35:24.583
Four years old.

35:26.126 --> 35:28.629
Said it taught him
the power of the imagination.

35:28.712 --> 35:30.839
Oh. That's very interesting.

35:30.923 --> 35:33.550
The power of the imagination,
think on that.

35:34.426 --> 35:36.803
A seed was planted and it grew from here.

35:38.222 --> 35:39.723
You know how I found that out?

35:41.642 --> 35:44.978
I got it from my professor friend
who knows everything about Scott Landon.

35:45.062 --> 35:49.191
His name is Dashmiel. It's a funny name.
It could be in one of Scott's books.

35:49.274 --> 35:52.319
But I call him Scott
'cause I feel like I-- I know him.

35:54.821 --> 35:56.823
By their work shall you know them.

35:57.991 --> 36:00.953
Sir, I really have to close now. So--

36:01.036 --> 36:02.204
Dashmiel.

36:03.372 --> 36:07.918
Dashmiel, like you're hungry, really
hungry, so you have to dash for a meal.

36:08.001 --> 36:10.587
Get it? Dashmiel, "dash for a meal."

36:11.088 --> 36:13.799
You know, you should put this book
in its own special case.

36:15.133 --> 36:19.471
With a little plaque underneath that says,

36:19.555 --> 36:21.682
"Scott Landon started here."

36:22.766 --> 36:26.478
So it could inspire generations to come.
What do you think?

36:28.397 --> 36:29.982
Yeah, I think that's a good idea.

36:32.484 --> 36:34.778
Sir, I really have to close up.

36:37.573 --> 36:38.574
You could…

36:40.951 --> 36:43.579
put it right here so all the children
could see it every day

36:43.662 --> 36:44.872
and get inspired by it.

36:45.455 --> 36:47.457
Yes. I think that's a good idea.

36:48.917 --> 36:50.460
I think we'll do it.

36:52.421 --> 36:53.505
Well…

36:58.886 --> 37:00.596
we see eye to eye on that.

37:06.268 --> 37:07.644
Campers forever.

37:07.728 --> 37:09.104
Campers forever.

37:10.772 --> 37:12.191
Beam me up, Scotty.

37:12.274 --> 37:13.567
Beam me up, Scotty.

37:18.655 --> 37:21.950
Dashmiel, dash for a meal. Think on
that 'cause there's something there.

37:22.034 --> 37:23.035
I will.

37:23.118 --> 37:24.786
And put that book in its own special case.

37:24.870 --> 37:26.413
That's a fine idea.

37:26.496 --> 37:28.582
This place ain't here
because of that bitch he married.

37:28.665 --> 37:30.042
It's here 'cause of him.

37:37.299 --> 37:39.343
I said Doctor

37:41.512 --> 37:43.347
Mr. M.D.

37:44.723 --> 37:46.558
Won't you tell me

37:48.352 --> 37:49.937
What's wrong with me

37:54.483 --> 37:56.151
I said Doctor

37:58.362 --> 37:59.780
Mr. M.D.

38:30.269 --> 38:32.938
Okay. All right.

38:34.106 --> 38:35.482
We're gonna go again. Ready?

38:36.358 --> 38:37.609
Count of three.

38:37.693 --> 38:41.321
One. Two. Three.

38:41.405 --> 38:43.657
And-- Come on, babe.

38:45.033 --> 38:46.034
Manda.

38:46.785 --> 38:47.786
Mrs. Landon.

38:47.870 --> 38:51.081
Hi. Yes, this is Lisa. Lisey.

38:51.164 --> 38:55.711
Mrs. Landon, let me begin by saying
how sorry I am for your loss.

38:56.378 --> 38:58.547
Your husband signed
several of his books for me,

38:58.630 --> 39:02.509
and they are among
my most treasured possessions.

39:02.593 --> 39:05.345
Thank you, Dr. Alberness.
That's very, very kind of you.

39:05.429 --> 39:09.224
Now my guess is you are calling
about your sister, Amanda Debusher.

39:10.142 --> 39:11.226
How'd you know that?

39:11.310 --> 39:14.062
Scott would--
He invited me to lunch three years ago.

39:14.646 --> 39:17.816
He said his sister-in-law
had suffered a bout of self-harm.

39:18.901 --> 39:19.943
Yeah, cutting.

39:20.569 --> 39:23.906
Yes. Followed by semi-catatonia.

39:24.907 --> 39:27.826
He said he believed those behaviors
might recur. Is that the case?

39:27.910 --> 39:32.831
It is. But Dr. Alberness--

39:32.915 --> 39:34.082
Call me Hugh.

39:35.334 --> 39:39.630
He left your number
in Amanda's address book for me to find.

39:39.713 --> 39:41.173
Probably just a precaution.

39:41.840 --> 39:44.092
We toured the facility here
after our lunch.

39:44.885 --> 39:48.138
And I promised that if your sister
suffered the break with reality

39:48.222 --> 39:51.099
-Scott feared might come--
-That you'd find a place for her.

39:52.643 --> 39:53.727
Yes.

39:54.770 --> 39:56.563
He must have loved her very much.

39:57.231 --> 39:59.024
He loved both of my sisters.

39:59.983 --> 40:02.903
Let me expedite this situation
for you, Mrs. Landon.

40:02.986 --> 40:06.657
I-- I'd love to do something for
my favorite writer. And-- And his widow.

40:08.700 --> 40:11.161
Thank-- Thank you, thank you.
I really appreciate that.

40:11.245 --> 40:14.081
So if you'll just connect me with
your accounts department,

40:14.164 --> 40:15.582
then I can arrange for payment.

40:18.627 --> 40:20.712
Your husband arranged for payment himself.

40:22.005 --> 40:25.008
He said all I had to do was make a call
and the fees would be paid.

40:25.592 --> 40:27.302
Yeah, yeah. Yeah. Thank you.

40:27.386 --> 40:29.763
-He was a generous man.
-Thank you. I appreciate that.

40:29.847 --> 40:31.473
Of-- Of course, of course.

40:56.373 --> 40:59.376
I should've told you this
before we got married.

41:02.212 --> 41:05.966
I don't wanna talk about
anything serious. It's so nice in here.

41:06.049 --> 41:09.970
Do you remember that night I cut myself
and you asked if I was crazy?

41:12.764 --> 41:14.057
I have visions.

41:15.559 --> 41:18.103
I write them down
and people pay to read them.

41:19.104 --> 41:21.857
But you're a writer. It's your job.

41:21.940 --> 41:27.571
You asked me about my family,
my daddy and my brother.

41:30.199 --> 41:32.326
And you said those were hard memories.

41:34.119 --> 41:35.204
They are.

42:10.697 --> 42:12.157
Take good care of her.

42:12.699 --> 42:13.784
We will, ma'am.

42:22.626 --> 42:23.961
How did he know?

42:25.379 --> 42:26.630
How did Scott know?

42:28.674 --> 42:29.675
I don't know.

42:45.774 --> 42:46.984
Hello?

42:47.067 --> 42:48.277
Mrs. Landon.

42:50.863 --> 42:53.198
Yeah. Yeah, who's this?

42:54.157 --> 42:55.409
Well, you can call me Jim.

42:55.492 --> 42:56.702
Jim who?

42:57.995 --> 42:59.079
How about Jim Dandy?

43:00.122 --> 43:03.500
Yeah, okay, I'm hanging up now, okay?

43:03.584 --> 43:05.711
Oh, come on, missus, I only want a minute.

43:07.713 --> 43:10.340
There's a man who came to see you
about your husband's papers.

43:10.424 --> 43:15.220
Oh, oh, okay. Yeah. Great. Great.

43:15.888 --> 43:18.807
You-- you-- you must
be a friend of Dashmiel's, huh?

43:18.891 --> 43:21.101
So is this a-- this a sales pitch?

43:21.685 --> 43:24.104
I guess you could call it
something like that, you see.

43:24.188 --> 43:27.816
-Yeah, no, I don't. I don't. I don't.
-Don't what?

43:27.900 --> 43:30.527
Because I thought that
I made myself perfectly clear.

43:30.611 --> 43:32.738
I mean, I thought I did. I guess I didn't.

43:32.821 --> 43:35.699
Maybe you and him didn't
get off to such a good start, but--

43:35.782 --> 43:38.535
Well, you could definitely say
that we didn't get off to a good start.

43:39.286 --> 43:43.165
Professor Dashmiel knows more about
Scott Landon than anyone else on Earth.

43:43.248 --> 43:46.752
God. He knows more?
So being married to him doesn't count?

43:46.835 --> 43:48.170
You don't think that counts?

43:48.253 --> 43:50.589
You don't know somebody when you're
married to them? That doesn't count?

43:50.672 --> 43:55.135
Maybe you do know that he said that
I was nothing but a restaurant hostess?

43:55.219 --> 43:56.220
What I mean to say is--

43:56.303 --> 43:57.888
Oh, God. Come on.

43:57.971 --> 44:01.725
Did I ask you to call?
Did I? Did I invite you to call me?

44:04.353 --> 44:05.562
No.

44:05.646 --> 44:07.731
No! No, I didn't.

44:07.814 --> 44:09.900
I didn't ask for this, please.

44:13.278 --> 44:15.405
Well, you're talking to me now
and not the prof,

44:15.489 --> 44:18.367
and I'm telling you you're
gonna give the prof what he wants.

44:19.826 --> 44:21.411
No ifs or maybe laters,

44:21.495 --> 44:24.414
you're gonna start by giving it to me,
and then I'm gonna give it to him.

44:24.998 --> 44:27.084
You had no right to Scott Landon.

44:27.167 --> 44:29.545
Not when he was alive
and not now that he's gone on.

44:30.420 --> 44:33.298
You never understood his greatness.
That's what the prof says.

44:33.382 --> 44:36.593
So you're gonna call him and
you're gonna tell him everything's okay.

44:36.677 --> 44:38.470
Yoko's giving up the goods.

44:38.554 --> 44:41.265
Yoko? Did you just--

44:42.516 --> 44:44.059
Did you just fucking call me Yoko?

44:44.685 --> 44:46.019
Now if that doesn't happen soon,

44:46.103 --> 44:48.522
I'm going to come to where you're at
and I'm going to hurt you in places

44:48.605 --> 44:51.233
you didn't allow the boys to
touch at junior high dances.

44:52.776 --> 44:53.777
Missus.

44:56.864 --> 44:58.991
Do you understand what I'm saying to you?

44:59.825 --> 45:00.826
Yeah.

45:01.618 --> 45:02.786
Mrs. Landon?

45:03.954 --> 45:05.122
Jim.

45:06.874 --> 45:09.543
-Yes, missus?
-Can you hear me?

45:10.460 --> 45:13.005
Well, you're a little low-pitched,
but yes, I can hear you.

45:19.678 --> 45:21.013
Go fuck yourself!

47:04.533 --> 47:06.618
-He's got a gun.
-Shooter!

47:06.702 --> 47:08.954
-A shooter! Gun!
-You stole my stories.

47:09.580 --> 47:11.248
You stole my mind.

47:21.175 --> 47:22.551
It's very close, honey.

47:25.345 --> 47:26.638
There's many faces.

47:26.722 --> 47:30.934
I don't understand.
I don't-- I don't understand.

47:32.311 --> 47:33.896
You know.

47:34.646 --> 47:36.106
You know.

47:50.287 --> 47:51.663
Long boy.

47:52.122 --> 47:53.540
Shut the fuck up.

47:54.917 --> 47:56.835
It makes a sound.

48:14.561 --> 48:17.606
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
That didn't happen.

48:19.233 --> 48:20.692
You know.
